{"questionId":"9073978","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Monochromatic light of wavelength <em>λ</em> is normally incident on a diffraction grating.&nbsp;The diagram shows adjacent slits of the diffraction grating labelled V, W and X.&nbsp;Light waves are diffracted through an angle <em>θ</em> to form a <strong>second-order</strong> diffraction&nbsp;maximum. Points Z and Y are labelled.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/cb743e6bc640488285fe359d106ce67c1b2e950a.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The separation of adjacent slits is <em>d</em>. Show that for the second-order diffraction&nbsp;maximum <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>«</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>XZ</mtext><mtext>VX</mtext></mfrac><mo>»</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p><em><br>Do <strong>not</strong> award <strong>ECF</strong> from(a)(ii).</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073978","referenceCode":"21M.2.HL.TZ2.8a.iii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The separation of adjacent slits is d. Show that for the second-order diffraction maximum 2λ=dsin θ.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.3 – Interference","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}